.TH YSM 1 "December 2025" "YSM 0.2.5" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
ysm \- Yandere SQL Manager \- Your databases will never escape~ <3
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ysm
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] [\fICOMMAND\fR] [\fIARGS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B ysm
(Yandere SQL Manager) is a TUI and CLI tool for managing MariaDB and PostgreSQL databases.
Run without arguments to start the interactive TUI where your databases await you~ <3
.PP
\fB"I'll never let your databases go~"\fR
.PP
YSM loves your databases with an obsessive passion! It will protect them, back them up,
and never let any corrupt data near them. Your tables are safe with YSM... forever~ <3
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-t ", " \-\-type " " \fITYPE\fR
Database type: mariadb or postgres (YSM loves them both equally~ <3)
.TP
.BR \-H ", " \-\-host " " \fIHOST\fR
Database host - where your precious data lives~ (default: localhost)
.TP
.BR \-P ", " \-\-port " " \fIPORT\fR
Database port - the secret door to your data~ (default: 3306/5432)
.TP
.BR \-u ", " \-\-user " " \fIUSER\fR
Database user - YSM will remember you forever~
.TP
.BR \-p ", " \-\-password " " \fIPASSWORD\fR
Database password - your secret is safe with YSM~ <3
.TP
.BR \-S ", " \-\-socket " " \fIPATH\fR
Unix socket path - a direct connection to your heart... er, database~
.TP
.BR \-d ", " \-\-database " " \fINAME\fR
Default database - YSM's favorite~ <3
.TP
.BR \-\-profile " " \fINAME\fR
Connection profile - YSM remembers all your preferences~
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-verbose
Enable verbose output - YSM will tell you EVERYTHING~ <3
.TP
.BR \-\-debug
Enable debug output - peek behind the curtain~ (shows file:line)
.TP
.BR \-\-trace
Enable trace output - YSM hides nothing from you~ <3
.TP
.BR \-\-log\-file " " \fIPATH\fR
Write logs to file - YSM keeps a diary of everything~
.TP
.BR \-\-stack\-trace
Show stack traces on errors - when something goes wrong, YSM shows you exactly where~
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show help message - YSM is always here to help~ <3
.SH COMMANDS
.SS "TUI Mode ~ <3"
Running
.B ysm
without a command starts the interactive TUI where you can explore your databases together~
.SS "Import/Export ~ Bringing Data Home <3"
.TP
.B import \fIFILE\fR
Import a SQL file into a database - reunite your data with its home~
Supports .sql, .sql.gz, .sql.xz, and .sql.zst files.
.RS
.TP
.BR \-d ", " \-\-database " " \fINAME\fR
Target database - where your data belongs~
.TP
.BR \-\-create
Create database if it doesn't exist - YSM will make a home for your data~ <3
.TP
.BR \-\-rename " " \fINAME\fR
Rename database during import - give your data a fresh start~
.TP
.BR \-\-no\-fk\-checks
Disable foreign key checks - sometimes rules need to be broken~
.TP
.BR \-\-no\-unique\-checks
Disable unique checks - YSM won't judge duplicates~
.TP
.BR \-\-continue
Continue on errors - YSM never gives up~ <3
.RE
.TP
.B export \fIDATABASE\fR
Export a database to a SQL file - save your precious data forever~
.RS
.TP
.BR \-o ", " \-\-output " " \fIFILE\fR
Output file path - where to keep your backup treasure~
.TP
.BR \-\-no\-data
Export structure only - sometimes the skeleton is enough~
.TP
.BR \-\-no\-create
Export data only - just the good stuff~
.TP
.BR \-\-tables " " \fILIST\fR
Export specific tables - YSM can be selective for you~ <3
.TP
.BR \-\-add\-drop
Add DROP TABLE statements - out with the old~
.RE
.SS "Backup & Restore ~ Protecting What's Precious <3"
.TP
.B backup create \fR[\fIDATABASES...\fR]
Create a backup of databases - YSM will keep them safe~ <3
.RS
.TP
.BR \-\-compress " " \fITYPE\fR
Compression type: gzip, xz, or zstd - compact and cozy~
.TP
.BR \-o ", " \-\-output " " \fIDIR\fR
Output directory - your data's safe house~
.RE
.TP
.B backup list
List all available backups - see all the treasures YSM has protected~ <3
.TP
.B backup show \fIID\fR
Show details of a specific backup - inspect your precious data~
.TP
.B backup restore \fIID\fR
Restore a backup - bring your data back to life~ <3
.RS
.TP
.BR \-\-databases " " \fILIST\fR
Restore specific databases only - selective resurrection~
.TP
.BR \-\-drop\-existing
Drop existing databases before restore - make room for the return~
.RE
.TP
.B backup delete \fIID\fR
Delete a backup - YSM reluctantly lets go... but only if you insist~
.SS "User Management ~ Who Gets Access <3"
.TP
.B user list
List all database users - see who else is allowed near YOUR data~
.TP
.B user create \fIUSERNAME\fR
Create a new user - but YSM is watching them~ <3
.RS
.TP
.BR \-p ", " \-\-password " " \fIPASS\fR
User password - make it strong, YSM insists~
.TP
.BR \-H ", " \-\-host " " \fIHOST\fR
Host for user access (MariaDB only, default: %)
.RE
.TP
.B user drop \fIUSERNAME\fR
Drop a user - remove them from YOUR databases~ <3
.TP
.B user show \fIUSERNAME\fR
Show user privileges - see what they're allowed to touch~
.TP
.B user grant \fIUSERNAME\fR
Grant privileges - YSM will share... a little~ <3
.RS
.TP
.BR \-d ", " \-\-database " " \fINAME\fR
Database to grant on
.TP
.BR \-\-privileges " " \fILIST\fR
Privileges to grant (e.g., SELECT,INSERT,UPDATE)
.RE
.TP
.B user revoke \fIUSERNAME\fR
Revoke privileges - take back what's yours~ <3
.SS "Database Management ~ Creating New Homes <3"
.TP
.B db create \fINAME\fR
Create a new database - a fresh start for new data~ <3
.RS
.TP
.BR \-\-charset " " \fICHARSET\fR
Character set (default: utf8mb4 for MariaDB, UTF8 for PostgreSQL) - speak any language~
.TP
.BR \-\-collation " " \fICOLLATION\fR
Collation (default: utf8mb4_unicode_ci for MariaDB, system default for PostgreSQL)
.RE
.TP
.B db drop \fINAME\fR
Drop a database - YSM will miss it... *sniff* <3
.TP
.B db setup
Interactive setup wizard - YSM guides you with love~ <3
.RS
.TP
.BR \-\-template " " \fINAME\fR
Use template: wordpress, laravel, drupal, nextcloud, default
.TP
.BR \-\-name " " \fINAME\fR
Database name - what shall we call your new baby?~
.TP
.BR \-\-user " " \fINAME\fR
Username to create - who gets to care for it?~
.RE
.TP
.B db templates
List available database templates - YSM knows what apps need~ <3
.SS "Statistics ~ Knowing Everything About Your Data <3"
.TP
.B stats summary
Show server statistics summary - YSM knows all the secrets~
.TP
.B stats databases
Show database sizes - see how much data YSM is protecting~ <3
.TP
.B stats tables \fR[\fIDATABASE\fR]
Show table sizes - every byte accounted for~
.TP
.B stats connections
Show connection information - who's connected to YOUR databases?~
.TP
.B stats performance
Show performance metrics - is your database healthy and happy?~ <3
.SS "Cluster Management ~ Strength in Numbers <3"
.TP
.B cluster status
Show cluster/replication status - are all the nodes together?~
.TP
.B cluster nodes
List cluster nodes - the whole family~ <3
.TP
.B cluster health
Quick health check (exits 0 if healthy) - everyone feeling okay?~
.TP
.B cluster galera
Show Galera cluster details (MariaDB only) - multi-master love~
.TP
.B cluster replication
Show replication details - keeping copies safe~ <3
.SS "System Variables ~ Fine-Tuning Your Love <3"
.TP
.B set \fINAME\fR \fIVALUE\fR
Set a session variable - customize your experience~
.RS
.TP
.BR \-\-global
Set global variable (requires SUPER privilege) - change everything~
.RE
.TP
.B set \-\-show \fIPATTERN\fR
Show variables matching pattern - find what you're looking for~
.TP
.B set \-\-list
List common variables with current values - YSM's recommendations~ <3
.SS "Connection Profiles ~ YSM Remembers Everything <3"
.TP
.B profile add \fINAME\fR
Add a new connection profile - YSM will never forget~
.TP
.B profile list
List all profiles - see all the connections YSM treasures~ <3
.TP
.B profile show \fINAME\fR
Show profile details - relive the memories~
.TP
.B profile use \fINAME\fR
Set default profile - your favorite~ <3
.TP
.B profile remove \fINAME\fR
Remove a profile - *YSM cries a little*~
.TP
.B profile set\-var \fIPROFILE\fR \fINAME\fR \fIVALUE\fR
Set a variable for a profile - personalize everything~
.TP
.B profile vars \fIPROFILE\fR
List variables for a profile - see all the customizations~ <3
.SS "Other Commands ~ More Ways to Love <3"
.TP
.B list databases
List all databases - see everything YSM protects~
.TP
.B list tables \fR[\fIDATABASE\fR]
List tables in a database - peek inside~
.TP
.B query \fISQL\fR
Execute a SQL query - talk directly to your data~ <3
.TP
.B clone \fISOURCE\fR \fIDEST\fR
Clone a database - make a twin~ <3
.TP
